Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, cut the @mature Cheddar cheese{30%g} into even chunks. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a large #bowl{}, combine the @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g}, garlic and @panko breadcrumbs{10%g}, then add the @British beef mince{240%g}. Season with salt and pepper, then mix together with your hands.

Roll the mince into even-sized balls. Shape into 2cm thick burgers around a chunk of cheese, ensuring they're well sealed, 1 per person.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the burgers and the @British streaky bacon rashers{4} onto a #baking tray{} (use another tray if necessary).

Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the burgers are cooked through and the bacon is golden brown and crispy, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Cook bacon thoroughly.

== Balsamic Pea Shoot Salad ==

While the burgers cook, put the @balsamic glaze{12%g} and @olive oil{for the dressing} in a #medium bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper. Set aside.

== To Serve ==

When the wedges and burgers are almost cooked, halve the @burger buns{2}.

Pop onto a baking tray and into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, pop the buns on your plates and spread a little @mayonnaise{2%g} over the cut sides. Top the base with a burger, 2 bacon rashers and a handful of @pea shoots{40%g}.

> TIP: Scoop up any escaped cheese from the baking tray and pile on top.

Add the remaining pea shoots to the bowl with the dressing and toss to coat.

Serve your melt in the middle burgers with the wedges and salad alongside.

Enjoy!